Name: GeographicStructureName
Description: A name for the GeographicStructure. May be expressed in multiple languages. Repeat the element to express names with different content, for example different names for different systems.

Name: Label
Description: A display label for the GeographicStructure. Supports multiple language versions of the same content as well as optional formatting of the content. Repeat for labels with different content, for example, labels with differing length limitations.

Name: Description
Description: A description of the GeographicStructure. Supports multiple language versions of the same content as well as optional formatting of the content.

Name: AuthorizedSource
Description: An identifiable authorization source repeated for each identifying code type. This allows the codes to be used as representations for response domains and value representations by designating a specific set of locations and the code of an authorization source. An authorization source should differentiate between codes derived for different purposes within the same agency.

Name: GeographicLevel
Description: Used to describe any level of geography, including overall coverage and each of the lower levels.

Name: GeographicLevelReference
Description: Inclusion of an existing GeographicLevel description by reference.
